Ad Text:
About Us

Join us at Cleanaway and contribute to making a sustainable future possible, together.

We transform waste into resources and renewable energy.  When you start to think of waste as a resource, it opens a world of possibilities.

As a high growth, ASX listed organisation with over 10,000 employees, our goal is to be recognised by our customers as the most innovative and sustainable waste management company with industry leading HSE performance.  We are Australia’s largest company in this sector, providing essential services to millions of customers and communities nationally.

The Opportunity

We are seeking a highly capable Power BI Developer to design, build and evolve robust semantic models, data pipelines and reporting solutions that deliver trusted, scalable and insight-driven outcomes across the enterprise. Sitting at the intersection of analytics engineering and business intelligence, this role combines strong Power BI expertise with data engineering capability to deliver high-quality, governed and performant analytics solutions.

Working closely with Data Engineers, Analysts and business stakeholders, you will translate complex requirements into scalable data and reporting solutions while contributing to data governance and platform optimisation. As our analytics capability matures, you will also leverage Generative AI and AI-assisted development tools to accelerate solution delivery, optimise DAX and SQL development, automate documentation and enhance insight generation across Cleanaway’s data ecosystem.

In this role, you will:

Design, develop and maintain Power BI semantic models, reports and dashboards aligned to enterprise standards
Develop and optimise data pipelines, ETL/ELT processes and curated data models to support analytics consumption
Partner with stakeholders to gather and translate requirements into scalable BI and analytics solutions
Implement dimensional data models (star schemas) to support performant enterprise reporting
Integrate Power BI with Snowflake, Azure (including Synapse / Data Lake) and on-premise data sources
Monitor and optimise semantic model performance (DAX, storage, refresh, capacity utilisation)
Utilise Gen AI and AI-assisted tooling to accelerate development, automate repetitive tasks, enhance documentation and improve insight discovery

About You

Proven experience developing Power BI semantic models and advanced DAX measures
Strong capability in SQL and data transformation, with experience building or supporting ETL/ELT pipelines
Solid understanding of dimensional modelling (Kimball / star schema design)
Experience working with cloud-based data platforms such as Snowflake, Azure Synapse or similar
Working knowledge of Git and modern development practices (version control, CI/CD concepts)
Experience using tools such as Tabular Editor to optimise and manage semantic models
Demonstrated ability to balance business engagement with technical solution design
Interest in and practical exposure to AI-assisted development tools, automation, and modern analytics engineering practices
Strong analytical mindset with attention to detail, performance optimisation and scalable design

This is an excellent opportunity to play a pivotal role in advancing Cleanaway’s enterprise analytics capability – combining strong Power BI development, data engineering fundamentals and emerging AI-enabled practices to drive meaningful business outcomes.

Our Process

Our recruitment process involves a number of checks including, but not limited to, criminal history, medicals, drug & alcohol testing, as well as verification of qualifications, licences and right-to-work status.

We are dedicated to improving employment outcomes and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. We also welcome candidates of all ages, abilities, gender identities, experiences (including veterans), and cultural backgrounds.

If you require any adjustments during the recruitment process, please contact us by emailing inclusion@cleanaway.com.au.

Join us on our exciting journey towards a sustainable future.

Simply click the Apply button or visit https://www.cleanaway.com.au/about-us/careers and let's make a positive impact together.

Job Title: AI Engineer - GenAI / LLM / RAG / AI Agents
Ad Text:
AI Engineer – GenAI / LLM / RAG / AI Agents

North Sydney | Hybrid (3 days in office)
$180K + Super

The Opportunity

We’re partnering with a leading Australian financial services organisation investing heavily in enterprise-grade AI and automation.

This is a hands-on build role where you will design and deploy real AI solutions into production, not just PoCs. You’ll work on next-generation AI agents across voice and text, transforming customer and internal workflows at scale.

If you want to move beyond experimentation and own end-to-end delivery of agentic AI systems in a secure, enterprise environment, this is the role.

What You’ll Be Doing

Designing and building AI agents for voice and text automation

Developing and optimising RAG pipelines for enterprise knowledge retrieval

Implementing LLM-powered workflows in production

Working with the Microsoft Azure AI ecosystem, including:

Azure OpenAI

Copilot Studio

Azure AI Foundry

Integrating AI into core platforms and business processes

Ensuring scalability, performance, and security of AI solutions

Partnering with stakeholders to turn real use cases into deployed outcomes

What We’re Looking For
Essential Experience

Proven track record delivering LLM / GenAI applications into production

Strong hands-on experience with RAG architectures

Experience building AI agents / autonomous workflows

Microsoft AI stack experience (Azure OpenAI, Copilot Studio, AI Foundry)

Strong engineering capability in Python or TypeScript / Node.js

API integration and microservices architecture

Deep understanding of:

Prompt engineering

Embeddings

Vector databases

Nice to Have

Voice / conversational AI experience

AI evaluation, guardrails, and safety frameworks

Experience in regulated or enterprise environments

MLOps / CI/CD for AI workloads

What’s In It For You

Greenfield AI program with strong executive backing

Build production-grade agentic AI solutions used across the business

High-impact, high-visibility role
